sentences: Ya Kid K (born Manuela Barbara Kamosi Moaso Djogi, 26 January 1972) is a Congoleseâ€“Belgian hip hop recording artist.
At the age of 11, Djogi moved to Belgium, later moving to Chicago (where she explored hip-hop, and the emerging sounds of house music), and later moved to Dallas, Texas.
After moving back to Belgium from the US, Ya Kid K helped form a hip hop label called Fresh Beat Productions.
She was part of the dance project Technotronic, which debuted with a major worldwide hit in 1989, "Pump Up the Jam".
(Before the Night Is Over)" was Ya Kid K's debut music video with Technotronic.
In 1992, Technotronic and Ya Kid K had a hit with "Move This," another single from 1989's Pump Up the Jam: The Album.
In 1991, Ya Kid K appeared on the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles II:
In 1995, Technotronic re-emerged in the U.S. with Ya Kid K as its front vocalist, again with limited success of the album, Recall.
In 1996, a Ya Kid K single titled "Rock My World" was released.
In 1997, Ya Kid K also provided fresh vocals for the 2 Skinnee J's cover of "Pump Up the Jam" entitled, "BBQ".
In October 2005, Ya Kid K made a guest appearance on Public Warning the debut album of English female rapper Lady Sovereign.
